Description from the publisher:

Intervention is the fourth Data Pack in the Flashpoint Cycle for Android: Netrunner, and its sixty cards (three copies each of twenty different cards) deposit you in the streets of New Angeles in the wake of the Twenty-Three Seconds incident. The economy is in free fall not just in New Angeles, but worldswide. For days the city lurches deeper into chaos. There are riots. There are kidnappings. And then the corps open fire on each other&hellip;

There's damage everywhere in Intervention. Meat damage, brain damage, and collateral damage. In keeping with the themes and aggressive stances of the Flashpoint Cycle, Intervention continues to provide us access to a set of desperate corps forced to show their teeth. We also find a new Haas-Bioroid identity, a new Shaper identity, a handful of Runner cards that dare you to run despite the risks, and a place of sanctuary in which the Runners can hide.

The official board game of Zecchino d'Oro: a TV Show competition where small children sing a song.
Players have to perform some tests to earn tiles to complete their mini puzzles.
The current player rolls the die and, depending on the square he lands, perform one of the following tests:

     Answer to a curiosity concerning the Zecchino d'Oro and its most famous songs;
     Complete the verse of a song, choosing one of three options proposed;
     Sing, mime or draw a song, so the other players can guess it;
     Draw 2 cards with images and invents a verse by being inspired by them.


If the test is successful, the current player can find out 2 tiles placed on the table: if they belong to his minipuzzle, he can keep them, otherwise he puts them in their place, always face down. Anyone can try to remember the location of their tiles, to discover them during his turn.
The player who completes their mini puzzle first, is the winner.

Three new elements to be added to the game:


     different strategy cards with a variant increasing maintenance costs;
     Deus Ex Machina cards: one-time events at a cost of VPS;
     Alternate random events

You play as one of the heads of a three-headed dragon named
Josh who has captured the Princess. You and the other
players, i.e. the dragon&rsquo;s other heads, will have to deal with
endless daring knights, a horde of the Princess&rsquo; defenders
and loads of other challenges, all while flirting with a lovely
Princess. Try not to let the dragon down and do your best to
stick with him until the end. That means not spending all your
money, or charming the capricious damsel more than the
other heads.

Gameplay: there is an event every turn that requires the attention of a dragon (for example, if you are attacked by a knight, or there is a thunderstorm, or if something like that happens). Each player-head suggests a solution (basically, it all boils down to an auction to minimize the resources needed). Those who can solve the problem with the least effort win the favor of the princess. If the problem appears insoluble, the entire dragon suffers &ndash; for example, a knight hits it hard with a sword. A few turns &ldquo;lost&rdquo; this way end the game. In the end, this is a balance between the cooperative part (benefits the entire dragon) and the individual one (to become the most efficient manager among other heads). And, of course, the princess herself occasionally assigns tasks &ndash; and the princess&rsquo;s card additionally defines which methods she likes most.

Contents:
&bull; 9 player cards (dragon heads);
&bull; 3 two-sided princess cards
(six beauties in all);
&bull; 30 dragonfire cards;
&bull; 15 spell cards;
&bull; 8 defense cards;
&bull; 7 gift cards;
&bull; 18 cards with daring adventurers
to defeat;
&bull; 6 unexpected move or
&ldquo;force majeure&rdquo; cards;
&bull; 6 tokens representing
Gosha&rsquo;s health;
&bull; 24 coins;
&bull; rules.

Les Jeux de 20 Heures is based on the immensely popular French television game show of the same name. The show, which ran from 1976 to 1987 on the FR3 network, mixed celebrity contestants with ordinary people from a different region of France each week.

The rules for the board game include four quiz formats used on the TV show, all based on words and sentences:

La phrase de Maitre Capello, where one contestant makes up a short sentence and the others are given clues to try to figure it out;

Si je vous dis, where contestants are given an eight-letter word and must try to come up with as many other words as possible using that word's letters only once;

L'adverbe, where players try to guess an adverb drawn at random by asking questions; and

Le mot de la fin, where one player chooses a six to eight letter secret word, and the rest try to work out that word by proposing other words and getting feedback on which letters of the proposed word are either in the right place or included elsewhere in the secret word.

Description from the publisher:

When one reporter's sensational news about a series of savage killings fails to make its way into the Arkham Advertiser, your friend at that establishment decides to contact you, nonetheless, deeming the reports the sort of thing that might suit your eccentric curiosities. She's right, of course, and when you head to Northside Station to book your ticket for New Orleans, you can't possibly imagine the full shape of the horrors that await you&hellip;

Designed to be played as a standalone adventure, or added to your Arkham Horror: The Card Game campaign as a "side-story," Curse of the Rougarou sends you along a bone-chilling hunt through New Orleans and the bayous of southern Louisiana. Its 62 cards come with all the rules, locations, act, agenda, and encounter cards that you'll need to immerse yourself in a mystery full of malign spirits, murderous beasts, and other hazards&mdash;some natural and some decidedly unnatural.

Pizza Express is a cooperative game of observation and quick reflexes.
The head pizza maker has been absent and the players, who are his assistants, must realize the pizzas without him.
A player, who plays the role of coordinator, takes the orders and talk to other players, who will try to realize more pizzas as possible, taking the right ingredients on the table before time runs out.
If the players, after several rounds, complete all the requested pizzas before the head comes back, win!
The game features 4 modes of play:
1) cooperative version, described above;
2) single-handed: the player plays both roles, taking the orders and trying to complete them;
3) teams: competitive version in which 2-4 teams try to complete the pizzas before the others;
4) all against all: competitive version in which everyone plays alone.

A mini-expansion for Great Scott! - The Game of Mad Invention, Commissions adds 24 new cards and a new way to score.

Instead of building inventions willy-nilly, with Commissions you have targets to aim for. Match the cards in your invention with the icons shown on a Commission card to claim its bonus points &ndash; as long as your invention does what the commissioner wants it to do&hellip;

The Commissions expansion is included as an exclusively free extra in Kickstarter editions of Great Scott!, but is also available separately.

WORLD AT WAR 85, VOLUME 3: THE UNTOLD BATTLES

The British General Heading up NATO&rsquo;s military command continued. &ldquo;We need reinforcements&hellip;now. How far off are the French?&rdquo;

His Belgian aide responded quickly, the information at his fingertips. &ldquo;They are on the move as we speak, heading for their border with West Germany, sir. Just like they have been practicing with the Bundeswehr in recent years. But other of their forces are refusing to cross our &ndash; excuse me, the Belgian border as yet. They appear to be biding their time.&rdquo;

THE UNTOLD BATTLES is the third volume in The WORLD AT WAR 85 SERIES of games of fast and furious platoon-level combat. Set in 1985, in an alternate history of World War III, the Warsaw Pact armies having already stormed across the border of East Germany attempting to finish their conquest of West Germany, and continue their offensive into The Low Countries, France, and the rest of Free Europe.

The WORLD AT WAR 85 system features a unique combat system that involves die rolls by both attacking units and defending units, which keeps both players engaged throughout the game. Die rolls are compared and hits applied quickly, as all the information you need to fight your units is on the counters. No combat results table is necessary. Initiative, formation activation, random turn length, close air support and air cover are all integrated smoothly.

We&rsquo;re not even supposed to do things like this, the Police Captain thought. She did not give credence to the initial phone reports a half hour ago, but now the growl of approaching Cuban armored vehicles echoed in the streets among the buildings of her town. She continued to shout to her officers last moment, desperate instructions: &ldquo;Heads low! Stay behind the car doors or anything else solid. And if whatever we are hearing turns out to be way heavier than I think &ndash; if it shoots at you, don&rsquo;t hesitate to RUN back to the Rally Point.&rdquo; 

AMERICA BREACHED is the fourth volume in The WORLD AT WAR 85 SERIES of games of fast and furious platoon-level combat. The series is set in 1985, in an alternate history of World War III. With the Warsaw Pact armies deep into Western Europe, and war zones appearing around the world drawing away U.S. ground reinforcements, an unlikely yet powerful collection of allies seize the opportunity to storm across the Rio Grande in force, raiding deep into Texas, ostensibly to deny the U.S. parts of its oil resources. If they succeed in their goal, they potentially might disrupt U.S. military operations worldwide.

